[2026-03-18T12:34:12.490Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01HVEv8gYPvESUF75gWKrirD","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All 4 ideas saved successfully. Here's the summary:\n\n## Tony Stark Scan Complete — Audit Logging & Compliance\n\n**4 ideas generated and saved to Vibeman:**\n\n| # | Title | Category | Effort | Impact | Risk |\n|---|-------|----------|--------|--------|------|\n| 1 | Merkle hash-chained tamper-evident audit trail | functionality | 7 | 9 | 6 |\n| 2 | Causal correlation chains across audit events | functionality | 8 | 9 | 7 |\n| 3 | Behavioral anomaly detection on key access patterns | functionality | 8 | 10 | 7 |\n| 4 | Write-ahead audit replication to immutable external sink | performance | 8 | 9 | 8 |\n\n**Key structural constraints identified:**\n- **Audit integrity is trust-based, not cryptographic** — the SQLite table is append-only by convention, not by mathematical proof. Anyone with file access can alter history undetectably.\n- **Events are isolated rows with no causal links** — forensic investigation requires manual timestamp correlation across unstructured `detail` strings.\n- **Single-machine trust boundary** — audit.db lives on the same host as the orchestrator, so a compromised host = compromised audit trail.\n- **Passive recording only** — the audit system records events but never detects anomalous patterns, leaving the difference between normal operations and credential exfiltration invisible until post-incident review."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3167,"cache_read_input_tokens":42596,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3167},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4da3f18a-d7fc-4a07-a959-b6a153b41c3f","uuid":"88eedf1c-5471-4d4d-960c-ff12044763